sentence: What did the bird say after its cage fell apart? cheap cheap!
explanation: Cheap can mean low in cost or of poor quality.
first_new_sentence: The shirt was very cheap, so I decided to buy it.
second_new_sentence: The cheap workmanship made the table wobble.

sentence: What does dr. oz do when you throw scientific evidence at his head? ducks like a quack.
explanation: Duck can mean a waterfowl or to lower the head quickly.
first_new_sentence: The duck swam across the pond gracefully.
second_new_sentence: I had to duck to avoid hitting my head on the low ceiling.

sentence: Why did the radiologist break up with the gold digger? because he saw right through her.
explanation: Saw can mean to visualize with the eyes or to cut using a tool.
first_new_sentence: I saw a beautiful sunset at the beach.
second_new_sentence: I used a saw to cut the wood for the project.

sentence: Why was 6 afraid of 7? because 7 was arrested for manslaughter.
explanation: Seven can refer to the number or can suggest the idea of seven as an important or pivotal element.
first_new_sentence: I have seven apples in the basket.
second_new_sentence: The seven wonders of the world are a marvel to behold.

sentence: What type of bees provide milk? boobees (boobies)
explanation: Boob can refer to a breast or can mean a foolish person.
first_new_sentence: I saw a movie that made fun of the act of being a boob.
second_new_sentence: The design on the shirt was of a big boob in a cartoon style.

sentence: Note: The interpretations of the dual meanings are created based on common usages, and I have included only those jokes that feature words conforming to the specified criteria.
